  "text": "Notably, the TSC line that displayed the near equal maternal-to-paternal expression ratio for H19, TSC line BC.3, was the same line that displayed a maternal expression bias for Igf2 (Table 2) . Although no other known imprinted gene displayed a variation in PO bias as dramatic as Igf2, a handful of known imprinted genes, such as Osbpl5, Impact, Dhcr7, and Ddc, also were expressed with a mild PO bias in only five of six profiled TSC lines and as a result were not detected as significantly biased by edgeR (Table S1 ). Interindividual variation in imprinted gene expression was observed recently in mule and hinny trophoblast cells [CITATION_1] , and its documentation here in mouse TSCs lends support to the idea that such variation may be a conserved feature of genomic imprinting across mammals.",
